The paper involves the use of reinforcement learning to develop a market making agent, which falls under the category of machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves the use of simulations and control theory, which could fall under cs.TR (Robotics and Control) and cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science). Finally, the paper involves the study of market dynamics and trading, which could fall under cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems).
